<h1>How Much Does a Car Wrap Cost in Chicago?</h1>
<p>Vehicle wrap pricing depends on vehicle size, coverage level, and material quality. Here's what to expect in the Chicago market with <strong>premium cast vinyl</strong>:</p>

<table>
<thead><tr><th>Vehicle Type</th><th>Full Wrap</th><th>Partial Wrap</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Sedan / Coupe</td><td>$2,800 – $3,500</td><td>$1,400 – $2,200</td></tr>
<tr><td>SUV / Crossover</td><td>$3,200 – $4,200</td><td>$1,600 – $2,800</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cargo Van</td><td>$2,800 – $4,500</td><td>$1,500 – $2,800</td></tr>
<tr><td>Sprinter Van</td><td>$3,500 – $5,200</td><td>$2,200 – $3,500</td></tr>
<tr><td>Box Truck 16–22 ft</td><td>$4,500 – $7,500</td><td>$2,800 – $4,500</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p>These prices include <strong>design, print, premium cast vinyl (Avery Dennison MPI 1105 or 3M IJ180-CV3), UV overlaminate, and certified installation</strong>. Fleet discounts: 5% off 3–4 vehicles, 10% off 5–9, 15% off 10+.</p>
<p>Beware of shops quoting under $2,000 for a full car wrap — they're almost certainly using <strong>calendered vinyl</strong> that will fail within 1–2 years.</p>


